OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1776960675
OL,3,CFour people 'critically injured' after
OL,4,Ctwo trains crash head-on in Denmark
OL,6,FA large emergency response that has
OL,7,Fbeen rolled out, with at least 60
OL,8,Fpeople at the scene, said Martin
OL,9,FSchmidt, operations chief at the
OL,10,FGreater Copenhagen Fire Department.
OL,12,FTraffic around the site has been
OL,13,Fimpacted and people are being urged to
OL,14,Ffind alternative routes.
OL,16,FPhotos show the smashed front ends of
OL,17,Fthe trains, although both remain
OL,18,Fupright on the tracks.
